The paper discusses computational methods for interdisciplinary research in the HathiTrust digital library, which involves information retrieval (IR), natural language processing (NLP), and human-computer interaction (HCI) techniques. The paper also mentions the use of classification systems and mixed-membership topic models, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
